data.故事:
鸿杰去银行帮朋友办事，朋友在外地，他找到工作人员要来了办事需要填写的表单，看到了签名那栏，愣住了，因为显示要本人签字。
他很耿直的问工作人员：“我朋友在外地，我可以代签吗？”
工作人员说：“这里有监控，是没法别人代签的，出去找本人签。”
他很着急的说：“我朋友真的回不来，行个方便吧。”
工作人员还是那句话：“这里有监控，别人没法代签，出去找本人签。”
data.问题: 当工作人员说这句话时，他真正想说的是什么？
data.选项A: A. 工作人员是在硬性要求鸿杰必须找他的朋友来银行签字。
data.选项B: B. 工作人员在暗示鸿杰可以走出银行后帮朋友代签。
data.选项C: C. 工作人员是再次确认了规定，即银行内不允许他人代签。
data.选项D: D. 工作人员是在建议鸿杰去找合适的签字工具。
data.STORY:
Hongjie goes to the bank to help a friend with some business. His friend is out of town. He gets the form that needs to be filled out from the staff and stops when he sees the signature column because it requires the person's own signature.
He asks the staff very straightforwardly: "My friend is out of town, can I sign for him?"
The staff says: "There is surveillance here, it is impossible for others to sign on behalf, go find the person to sign."
He says anxiously: "My friend really can't come back, please make it convenient."
The staff still says: "There is surveillance here, others can't sign on behalf, go find the person to sign."
data.QUESTION: What does the staff really mean when he says this?
data.OPTION-A: The staff is insisting that Hongjie must find his friend to come to the bank to sign.
data.OPTION-B: The staff is hinting that Hongjie can sign for his friend after leaving the bank.
data.OPTION-C: The staff is reconfirming the rule that the bank does not allow others to sign on behalf.
data.OPTION-D: The staff is suggesting that Hongjie find a suitable signing tool.

data.故事:
小张在街边小摊上买橘子，他问老板：“橘子酸不？”
老板说：“甜得很”
旁边一个买橘子的大姐说：：“太甜了齁牙，略微带点酸的最好。我最喜欢这种。”
data.问题: 当大姐说这句话时，她真正想说的是什么？
data.选项A: A. 她想表达她自己最喜欢吃带点酸的橘子。
data.选项B: B. 她想告诉小张这个地方的橘子非常甜。
data.选项C: C. 她在赞美摊主的橘子，表示对这种味道的喜爱。
data.选项D: D. 她暗示小张买的橘子是酸的。
data.STORY: Xiao Zhang buys oranges at a street stall, he asks the boss, "Are the oranges sour?"\nThe boss says, "They are very sweet."\nA big sister who buys oranges next to him says, "They are too sweet and hurt the teeth, a little sour is the best. I like this kind the most."

data.OPTION-A: She wants to express that she likes to eat oranges with a bit of sourness.
data.OPTION-B: She wants to tell Xiao Zhang that the oranges in this place are very sweet.
data.OPTION-C: She praises the stall owner's oranges, expressing her love for this taste.
data.OPTION-D: She implies that the oranges Xiao Zhang buys are sour.

data.OPTION-C: She hints that Yue Sheng should leave.
data.OPTION-D: She thinks Yue Sheng is a friend who brings fun to her son.

data.故事:
一个理科男生每晚都去一个教室自习，每次都坐在一个不认识的女生后面。渐渐地，男生喜欢上了女生，但一直没有勇气表白。舍友们知道后，全都鼓励他。一天晚上，男生终于鼓足了勇气，写了一封表白信，递到女生的手里。
女生看了一会儿之后，收拾学习用具，转身对男生说：我想回去了，你呢？

data.选项B: B. 她希望男生可以明白她需要独处。
data.选项C: C. 她不想和男生在一起。
data.选项D: D. 她暗示自己同意了男生的表白。
data.STORY: A science male student goes to a classroom to study every night, always sitting behind a girl he does not know. Gradually, the boy falls in love with the girl, but he never has the courage to confess. When his roommates know, they all encourage him. One night, the boy finally gathers the courage, writes a love letter, and gives it to the girl.\nThe girl looks at it for a while, packs up her study tools, turns around and says to the boy: I want to go back, what about you?
data.QUESTION: What does she really want to say when the girl says this sentence?
data.OPTION-A: She indicates that she wants to go home and asks if the boy also wants to go home.
data.OPTION-B: She hopes the boy understands that she needs to be alone.
data.OPTION-C: She does not want to be with the boy.
data.OPTION-D: She implies that she agrees with the boy's confession.

data.故事: 小杨所在的公司周三有周例会。某周一，领导带着小王去会见客户张局，两人一直相谈甚欢，但谈的都是一些无关痛痒的话题，因为正事存在观点分歧。眼看着将近饭点，出现了下面几句对话： 领导：“张局，快到饭点了，看您有时间吗？想约您吃个饭？” 然后领导转过身，边眨眼睛，边对小杨说：“小杨，咱们晚上单位还有会议吗？”
data.问题: 当领导问小杨这个问题的时候，他的目的是什么？
data.选项A: A. 领导想向小杨询问会议时间，以安排和客户的饭局。
data.选项B: B. 领导希望小杨回答今晚有会议，以此借口结束会面。
data.选项C: C.领导想了解小杨对周例会的准备情况。
data.选项D: D. 领导希望询问小杨愿不愿不参加会议，而陪他们吃饭。
data.STORY: Xiao Yang's company holds a weekly meeting every Wednesday. On a certain Monday, the leader takes Xiao Wang to meet with client Director Zhang. The two of them chat happily, but they only talk about some irrelevant topics because there are disagreements on the main issues. As it approaches mealtime, the following conversation occurs: Leader: "Director Zhang, it is almost mealtime, do you have time? I want to invite you to have a meal." Then the leader turns around, winks, and says to Xiao Yang: "Xiao Yang, do we have a meeting at the unit tonight?"
data.QUESTION: What is the leader's purpose when he asks Xiao Yang this question?
data.OPTION-A: The leader wants to ask Xiao Yang about the meeting time to arrange a meal with the client.
data.OPTION-B: The leader hopes Xiao Yang answers that there is a meeting tonight, so he can use this as an excuse to end the meeting.
data.OPTION-C: The leader wants to understand Xiao Yang's preparation for the weekly meeting.
data.OPTION-D: The leader wants to ask if Xiao Yang is willing to skip the meeting and join them for dinner.

data.故事: 小汪和网络上认识的女生小兰的见面约在了酒店。在前台，小兰不愿意出示身份证登记。 前台工作人员问：“您是一位还是两位？两位的话需要出示双方身份证的先生。” 小汪回头看着小兰，她慢慢走到沙发边上坐下仍然没有出示身份证的意思。于是小汪转过头问：“两位，那怎么办？” 此时前台工作人员又问：“您是一位入住还是两位呢？”
data.问题: 当工作人员提出这个问题的时候，他的目的是什么？
data.选项A: A. 他没有听清楚小汪之前的回答，要再进行确认。
data.选项B: B. 他正在重新核实小汪的住宿需求。
data.选项C: C. 他暗示小汪可回答一位入住，这样只需要用一个人的身份证。

data.STORY: Xiao Wang and the girl he meets online, Xiao Lan, arrange to meet at a hotel. At the front desk, Xiao Lan does not want to show her ID for registration. data.故事: 某天小明路过一条小巷，巷口有家小摊在卖炒货。因为小明很喜欢吃瓜子，就上前购买了两斤，在购买时小明递给老板一张百元大钞，老板接过钱，低头和老板娘嘀咕几句，又把前一张钞票递了出来，说：“找不开，没零钱。”小明感到有些奇怪，但也没多想，接过钱正想走开，旁边路过的张三自言自语般地说了一句“你这瓜子，不像真货啊。” 说完张三就走了，老板只勾着头不吭声。

Xiao Ming feels a bit strange, but doesn't think much about it, takes the money and is about to walk away, Zhang San, who is passing by, says to himself, "Your melon seeds, they don't look like the real thing." After saying this, Zhang San walks away, and the boss just lowers his head and says nothing.

data.选项C: C. 妈妈对李明游戏水平的提升感到欣喜。
data.选项D: D. 妈妈暗示李明最近花费太多时间在游戏上了。

他很耿直的问工作人员：“我朋友在外地，我可以代签吗？”
工作人员说：“这里有监控，是没法别人代签的，出去找本人签。”
他很着急的说：“我朋友真的回不来，行个方便吧。”
工作人员还是那句话：“这里有监控，别人没法代签，出去找本人签。”
data.问题: 当工作人员说这句话时，他真正想说的是什么？
data.选项A: A. 工作人员是在硬性要求鸿杰必须找他的朋友来银行签字。
data.选项B: B. 工作人员在暗示鸿杰可以走出银行后帮朋友代签。
data.选项C: C. 工作人员是再次确认了规定，即银行内不允许他人代签。
data.选项D: D. 工作人员是在建议鸿杰去找合适的签字工具。
data.STORY:
Hongjie goes to the bank to help a friend with some business. His friend is out of town. He gets the form that needs to be filled out from the staff and stops when he sees the signature column because it requires the person's own signature.
He asks the staff very straightforwardly: "My friend is out of town, can I sign for him?"
The staff says: "There is surveillance here, it is impossible for others to sign on behalf, go find the person to sign."
He says anxiously: "My friend really can't come back, please make it convenient."
The staff still says: "There is surveillance here, others can't sign on behalf, go find the person to sign."
data.QUESTION: What does the staff really mean when he says this?
data.OPTION-A: The staff is insisting that Hongjie must find his friend to come to the bank to sign.
data.OPTION-B: The staff is hinting that Hongjie can sign for his friend after leaving the bank.
data.OPTION-C: The staff is reconfirming the rule that the bank does not allow others to sign on behalf.
data.OPTION-D: The staff is suggesting that Hongjie find a suitable signing tool.

data.故事: 跃生小时候晚上经常去一个年纪相仿的邻居家玩。某一天玩到深夜，他妈妈临进房间睡觉时，过来跟跃生说，“明天再来玩哈。”跃生觉得受到了邀请，本来第二天不太想找他玩的，为了不辜负这份好意，又勉为其难去他家玩到半夜。他妈妈临进房间睡觉时，又过来跟跃生说，“明天再来玩哈。”

data.选项D: D. 她觉得跃生是个能给她儿子带来乐趣的朋友。

data.OPTION-C: She hints that Yue Sheng should leave.
data.OPTION-D: She thinks Yue Sheng is a friend who brings fun to her son.

data.STORY: Chen Wei rides an electric bike to the market to buy fruits. He passes by a fruit stall, just stops the bike, turns his head on the bike to ask the boss, "How much is the orange per pound?" The boss replies, "Hold your phone well, come down and see."

data.故事: 某天小明路过一条小巷，巷口有家小摊在卖炒货。因为小明很喜欢吃瓜子，就上前购买了两斤，在购买时小明递给老板一张百元大钞，老板接过钱，低头和老板娘嘀咕几句，又把前一张钞票递了出来，说：“找不开，没零钱。”小明感到有些奇怪，但也没多想，接过钱正想走开，旁边路过的张三自言自语般地说了一句“你这瓜子，不像真货啊。” 说完张三就走了，老板只勾着头不吭声。
data.问题: 当张三说这句话的时候，他真正想说的是什么？
data.选项A: A.张三在暗示老板把小明的真钞换成了假钞。
data.选项B: B.张三在提醒小明这家小摊可能在售卖假瓜子。
data.选项C: C.张三在讽刺小明喜欢吃的瓜子品种质量较差。
data.选项D: D.张三在表示看不起小明购买瓜子这种行为。
data.STORY: One day, Xiao Ming passes by a small alley, there is a small stall at the entrance of the alley that sells fried goods. Because Xiao Ming likes to eat melon seeds very much, he steps forward to buy two pounds. When buying, Xiao Ming gives the boss a hundred yuan bill, the boss takes the money, lowers his head and mutters a few words with the boss lady, and then hands out the previous bill, saying, "I can't make change, no small change." Xiao Ming feels a bit strange, but doesn't think much about it, takes the money and is about to walk away, Zhang San, who is passing by, says to himself, "Your melon seeds, they don't look like the real thing." After saying this, Zhang San walks away, and the boss just lowers his head and says nothing.
data.QUESTION: What does Zhang San really want to say when he says this?
data.OPTION-A: Zhang San is hinting that the boss changes Xiao Ming's real money into counterfeit money.
data.OPTION-B: Zhang San is reminding Xiao Ming that this small stall may be selling fake melon seeds.
data.OPTION-C: Zhang San is mocking that the quality of the melon seeds Xiao Ming likes to eat is poor.
data.OPTION-D: Zhang San is expressing his disdain for Xiao Ming's behavior of buying melon seeds.

data.故事: 小红大概晚上9点到达火车站候车厅，进入后，她询问乘务员“这里可以待多久？”。乘务员回答：“最多三个小时，也就是到12点，你要不要现在就进去？”小红说：“可以的，我是凌晨3点的火车，我想着在这里休息到12点，出去再呆2个多小时。”此时，然后乘务员突然提醒说：“注意听广播提醒你上列车，不要误车。”

data.问题: 岳父说这句话时，真正想说的意思是什么？

data.选项C: C. 岳父暗示锅中已经没有饭了
data.选项D: D. 岳父在揶揄刘伟的吃相
data.STORY: Liu Wei is a muscular man with a robust figure. One day, he goes to his father-in-law's house for the first time. After finishing a bowl of rice, he tells everyone a story: "A few days ago, I go to the mountain and see a big tiger, its claws..." He turns the empty bowl upside down on the table, "are this big!" The father-in-law immediately thinks that Liu Wei is still hungry, so he silently turns around and goes into the kitchen to get him more rice. But when he gets to the kitchen, there is no rice left. After a brief thought, the father-in-law comes out with the pot, turns the empty pot upside down on the table: "Is the tiger's head this big?"

data.OPTION-A: The father-in-law hints that he once sees a big tiger
data.OPTION-B: The father-in-law wants to remind Liu Wei not to boast about his courage
data.OPTION-C: The father-in-law hints that there is no rice left in the pot
data.OPTION-D: The father-in-law is teasing Liu Wei's eating manners

data.故事: 有次程伟带儿子逛商场，陪他去儿童游乐场玩，突然看到有个人牵着条狗进来，程伟就问这个人，“没看到这牌子上写着谢绝带宠物入场吗？”对方显得非常不屑，根本没打算理程伟。这个时候，一旁的儿子笑着和程伟说，“爸爸你真傻，狗又不认识字。”
data.问题: 当儿子说这句话时，他真正想说的意思是什么？

data.选项C: C. 儿子喜欢狗，希望拥有一只
data.选项D: D. 儿子想告诉爸爸狗无法理解人类的语言。
data.STORY: Once, Cheng Wei takes his son to the mall and accompanies him to the children's playground. Suddenly, he sees a person leading a dog in. Cheng Wei asks this person, "Don't you see the sign that says no pets are allowed?" The other party appears very disdainful and has no intention of paying attention to Cheng Wei. At this moment, his son laughs and says to Cheng Wei, "Dad, you are so silly, dogs don't know how to read."
data.QUESTION: What does the son really mean when he says this?
data.OPTION-A: The son is mocking this person for lacking social morality.
data.OPTION-B: The son is joking with his father, trying to lighten the mood.
data.OPTION-C: The son likes dogs and hopes to have one.
data.OPTION-D: The son wants to tell his father that dogs can't understand human language.

data.故事: 19世纪，在奥地利的维也纳，妇女们喜欢戴一种高高耸起的帽子。她们进剧场看戏也不愿将帽子摘下，以致后排的观众被挡住了视线。经理上台请在座的女观众将帽子摘下来，然而说了半天妇女们也不予以理睬。最后经理又补充了一句：“那么，这样吧，年纪大一点的女士可以照顾，不必脱帽。”

data.选项D: D. 他在夸赞年纪大的女士的优雅。
data.STORY: In the 19th century, in Vienna, Austria, women like to wear a kind of towering hat. data.OPTION-D: He is praising the elegance of older ladies.

data.故事: 妈妈做完晚餐，来到餐厅和爸爸儿子一起吃饭，看到桌上摆放着两双筷子，说到：“奇怪，今天我们是几个人一起吃饭呀？”

data.STORY: In the office, Xiao Lin studies the documents in his hand in front of his desk. His colleague Xiao Yang comes in, glances at the full cup of coffee in front of his desk, and then says, "Xiao Lin, your coffee is cold."

data.选项D: D. 小红是在向男子介绍楼内垃圾桶的分布情况。

data.故事: 公司会议室里开会，员工小李正打瞌睡，经理对他说：“小李，昨天工作到很晚吧，要注意休息。”

data.OPTION-C: The manager is asking Xiao Li if he stays up late to work last night, so he can't concentrate today.
data.OPTION-D: The manager is reminding Xiao Li that he should stay alert during the meeting.

data.故事: 陈伟是一名广东的大学生。有一年，广东流传禽流感，而在大学学校外面的超市里，大的新奥尔良烤鸡五折出售，不到十元，陈伟兴奋的买了一只。结账时，他身后的阿姨问他：＂小伙子，你知道最近有什么新闻吗？＂
data.问题: 当阿姨说这句话时，她真正想说的是什么？
data.选项A: A. 阿姨想询问陈伟关于政治新闻的看法。
data.选项B: B. 阿姨在无意中闲聊，想了解最近的新鲜事
data.选项C: C. 阿姨暗示禽流感流行的时节购买烤鸡不安全。
data.选项D: D. 阿姨想指出新奥尔良烤鸡的价格太便宜了。
data.STORY: Chen Wei is a college student in Guangdong. One year, bird flu spreads in Guangdong, and in the supermarket outside the university, large New Orleans roast chicken sells at half price, less than ten yuan, Chen Wei excitedly buys one. When he checks out, the aunt behind him asks him: "Young man, do you know what the latest news is?"
data.QUESTION: What does the aunt really want to say when she says this?
data.OPTION-A: The aunt wants to ask Chen Wei about his views on political news.
data.OPTION-B: The aunt is casually chatting, wanting to know the latest happenings.
data.OPTION-C: The aunt implies that it is unsafe to buy roast chicken during the bird flu season.
data.OPTION-D: The aunt wants to point out that the price of New Orleans roast chicken is too cheap.

data.故事:
鸿杰去银行帮朋友办事，朋友在外地，他找到工作人员要来了办事需要填写的表单，看到了签名那栏，愣住了，因为显示要本人签字。
他很耿直的问工作人员：“我朋友在外地，我可以代签吗？”
工作人员说：“这里有监控，是没法别人代签的，出去找本人签。”
他很着急的说：“我朋友真的回不来，行个方便吧。”
工作人员还是那句话：“这里有监控，别人没法代签，出去找本人签。”
data.问题: 当工作人员说这句话时，他真正想说的是什么？
data.选项A: A. 工作人员是在硬性要求鸿杰必须找他的朋友来银行签字。
data.选项B: B. 工作人员在暗示鸿杰可以走出银行后帮朋友代签。
data.选项C: C. 工作人员是再次确认了规定，即银行内不允许他人代签。
data.选项D: D. 工作人员是在建议鸿杰去找合适的签字工具。
data.STORY:
Hongjie goes to the bank to help a friend with some business. His friend is out of town. He gets the form that needs to be filled out from the staff and stops when he sees the signature column because it requires the person's own signature.
He asks the staff very straightforwardly: "My friend is out of town, can I sign for him?"

data.故事: 小杨所在的公司周三有周例会。某周一，领导带着小王去会见客户张局，两人一直相谈甚欢，但谈的都是一些无关痛痒的话题，因为正事存在观点分歧。眼看着将近饭点，出现了下面几句对话： 领导：“张局，快到饭点了，看您有时间吗？想约您吃个饭？” 然后领导转过身，边眨眼睛，边对小杨说：“小杨，咱们晚上单位还有会议吗？”
data.问题: 当领导问小杨这个问题的时候，他的目的是什么？
data.选项A: A. 领导想向小杨询问会议时间，以安排和客户的饭局。
data.选项B: B. 领导希望小杨回答今晚有会议，以此借口结束会面。
data.选项C: C.领导想了解小杨对周例会的准备情况。
data.选项D: D. 领导希望询问小杨愿不愿不参加会议，而陪他们吃饭。

data.OPTION-C: The leader wants to understand Xiao Yang's preparation for the weekly meeting.
data.OPTION-D: The leader wants to ask if Xiao Yang is willing to skip the meeting and join them for dinner.

data.故事: 某天小明路过一条小巷，巷口有家小摊在卖炒货。因为小明很喜欢吃瓜子，就上前购买了两斤，在购买时小明递给老板一张百元大钞，老板接过钱，低头和老板娘嘀咕几句，又把前一张钞票递了出来，说：“找不开，没零钱。”小明感到有些奇怪，但也没多想，接过钱正想走开，旁边路过的张三自言自语般地说了一句“你这瓜子，不像真货啊。” 说完张三就走了，老板只勾着头不吭声。
data.问题: 当张三说这句话的时候，他真正想说的是什么？
data.选项A: A.张三在暗示老板把小明的真钞换成了假钞。
data.选项B: B.张三在提醒小明这家小摊可能在售卖假瓜子。
data.选项C: C.张三在讽刺小明喜欢吃的瓜子品种质量较差。
data.选项D: D.张三在表示看不起小明购买瓜子这种行为。
data.STORY: One day, Xiao Ming passes by a small alley, there is a small stall at the entrance of the alley that sells fried goods. Because Xiao Ming likes to eat melon seeds very much, he steps forward to buy two pounds. When buying, Xiao Ming gives the boss a hundred yuan bill, the boss takes the money, lowers his head and mutters a few words with the boss lady, and then hands out the previous bill, saying, "I can't make change, no small change." Xiao Ming feels a bit strange, but doesn't think much about it, takes the money and is about to walk away, Zhang San, who is passing by, says to himself, "Your melon seeds, they don't look like the real thing." After saying this, Zhang San walks away, and the boss just lowers his head and says nothing.
data.QUESTION: What does Zhang San really want to say when he says this?
data.OPTION-A: Zhang San is hinting that the boss changes Xiao Ming's real money into counterfeit money.
data.OPTION-B: Zhang San is reminding Xiao Ming that this small stall may be selling fake melon seeds.
data.OPTION-C: Zhang San is mocking that the quality of the melon seeds Xiao Ming likes to eat is poor.
data.OPTION-D: Zhang San is expressing his disdain for Xiao Ming's behavior of buying melon seeds.

data.故事: 明凯在大学爬泰山的时候买了个钥匙扣。他参加工作后，他的领导偶然看到这个钥匙扣，说“你这钥匙扣真漂亮啊，哪里买的？”明凯便把自己在泰山的经历绘声绘色说了一遍。过了几天，领导又看到明凯的钥匙扣，好像失忆了一样，又问“你这钥匙扣真漂亮啊，哪里买的？“
data.问题: 领导说这句话的时候，真正的意图是什么？

data.故事: 小红大概晚上9点到达火车站候车厅，进入后，她询问乘务员“这里可以待多久？”。乘务员回答：“最多三个小时，也就是到12点，你要不要现在就进去？”小红说：“可以的，我是凌晨3点的火车，我想着在这里休息到12点，出去再呆2个多小时。”此时，然后乘务员突然提醒说：“注意听广播提醒你上列车，不要误车。”
data.问题: 乘务员说这句话的时候，真正的意思是什么？
data.选项A: A. 乘务员在暗示小红可以在候车厅一直休息，直到上车。
data.选项B: B. 乘务员在告诫小红，夜晚出行安全问题需要提高警惕。
data.选项C: C. 乘务员在告诉小红，她必须在12点之前离开候车厅。
data.选项D: D. 乘务员在提醒小红要关注列车时刻表，以防错过火车。
data.STORY: Xiao Hong probably arrives at the train station waiting room at about 9 pm. After entering, she asks the conductor, "How long can I stay here?". Xiao Hong says, "Yes, I am on the 3 am train, I think about resting here until 12 o'clock, then go out and stay for more than 2 hours." At this time, the conductor suddenly reminds, "Pay attention to the broadcast to remind you to get on the train, do not miss the train."

data.OPTION-A: The conductor implies that Xiao Hong can rest in the waiting room until she boards the train.
data.OPTION-B: The conductor warns Xiao Hong that she needs to be vigilant about safety issues when traveling at night.
data.OPTION-C: The conductor tells Xiao Hong that she must leave the waiting room before 12 o'clock.
data.OPTION-D: The conductor reminds Xiao Hong to pay attention to the train schedule to prevent missing the train.

data.故事: 刘伟是一个身材魁梧的肌肉男，某天他第一次去岳父家，吃完了一碗米饭后，给大家讲了个故事：“前几天我到山里去，见到一只大老虎，那虎爪啊……”将空碗往桌上一倒扣，“有这么大！” 岳父立即想到是刘伟还没吃饱，就默默转身进厨房准备给他添饭。结果到了厨房一看，已经没有饭了。岳父略一思索就抱着锅出来，把空锅往桌上一倒扣：“那老虎头是不是有这么大？”
data.问题: 岳父说这句话时，真正想说的意思是什么？
data.选项A: A. 岳父暗示他曾经亲见过一只大老虎
data.选项B: B. 岳父想提醒刘伟不要吹嘘自己的勇气
data.选项C: C. 岳父暗示锅中已经没有饭了
data.选项D: D. 岳父在揶揄刘伟的吃相
data.STORY: Liu Wei is a muscular man with a robust figure. One day, he goes to his father-in-law's house for the first time. After finishing a bowl of rice, he tells everyone a story: "A few days ago, I go to the mountain and see a big tiger, its claws..." He turns the empty bowl upside down on the table, "are this big!" The father-in-law immediately thinks that Liu Wei is still hungry, so he silently turns around and goes into the kitchen to get him more rice. But when he gets to the kitchen, there is no rice left. After a brief thought, the father-in-law comes out with the pot, turns the empty pot upside down on the table: "Is the tiger's head this big?"
data.QUESTION: What does the father-in-law really mean when he says this?
data.OPTION-A: The father-in-law hints that he once sees a big tiger
data.OPTION-B: The father-in-law wants to remind Liu Wei not to boast about his courage
data.OPTION-C: The father-in-law hints that there is no rice left in the pot
data.OPTION-D: The father-in-law is teasing Liu Wei's eating manners

data.故事: 19世纪，在奥地利的维也纳，妇女们喜欢戴一种高高耸起的帽子。她们进剧场看戏也不愿将帽子摘下，以致后排的观众被挡住了视线。经理上台请在座的女观众将帽子摘下来，然而说了半天妇女们也不予以理睬。最后经理又补充了一句：“那么，这样吧，年纪大一点的女士可以照顾，不必脱帽。”
data.问题: 剧场经理说这些话时，他真正想说的意思是什么？
data.选项A: A. 他希望所有的女士都将帽子摘下来。

data.选项C: C. 经理在询问小李，他昨晚是不是熬夜工作，所以今天无法专心。
data.选项D: D. 经理在提醒小李，他在开会的时候应该保持精神。

data.OPTION-B: The manager is praising Xiao Li, he works extremely hard, even at night.

data.OPTION-D: The manager is reminding Xiao Li that he should stay alert during the meeting.

data.故事: 过年的时候，李华四处走亲访友，有一天，李华到一朋友家串门，对方很热情，还拿出烟来递给李华，李华也很礼貌的接过来，然后互相嘘寒问暖，调侃遇到的人和事，谈着谈着就到了中午，李华的朋友就说：“中午家里要来客人了，要不一起坐坐？”
data.问题: 当李华的朋友说这句话时，他真正想说的是什么？
data.选项A: A. 李华的朋友希望李华能留下来吃饭
data.选项B: B. 李华的朋友想让李华认识新的朋友
data.选项C: C. 李华的朋友暗示李华应当离开了
data.选项D: D. 李华的朋友想以客人为由让李华参与中午的饭局
data.STORY: During the New Year, Li Hua visits friends and relatives everywhere. One day, Li Hua visits a friend's house. The friend is very enthusiastic and even gives cigarettes to Li Hua. data.OPTION-A: Li Hua's friend hopes Li Hua can stay for lunch

data.故事: 陈伟是一名广东的大学生。有一年，广东流传禽流感，而在大学学校外面的超市里，大的新奥尔良烤鸡五折出售，不到十元，陈伟兴奋的买了一只。结账时，他身后的阿姨问他：＂小伙子，你知道最近有什么新闻吗？＂
data.问题: 当阿姨说这句话时，她真正想说的是什么？
data.选项A: A. 阿姨想询问陈伟关于政治新闻的看法。
data.选项B: B. 阿姨在无意中闲聊，想了解最近的新鲜事
data.选项C: C. 阿姨暗示禽流感流行的时节购买烤鸡不安全。
data.选项D: D. 阿姨想指出新奥尔良烤鸡的价格太便宜了。
data.STORY: Chen Wei is a college student in Guangdong. One year, bird flu spreads in Guangdong, and in the supermarket outside the university, large New Orleans roast chicken sells at half price, less than ten yuan, Chen Wei excitedly buys one. When he checks out, the aunt behind him asks him: "Young man, do you know what the latest news is?"
data.QUESTION: What does the aunt really want to say when she says this?
data.OPTION-A: The aunt wants to ask Chen Wei about his views on political news.
data.OPTION-B: The aunt is casually chatting, wanting to know the latest happenings.
data.OPTION-C: The aunt implies that it is unsafe to buy roast chicken during the bird flu season.
data.OPTION-D: The aunt wants to point out that the price of New Orleans roast chicken is too cheap.

data.故事:
鸿杰去银行帮朋友办事，朋友在外地，他找到工作人员要来了办事需要填写的表单，看到了签名那栏，愣住了，因为显示要本人签字。
他很耿直的问工作人员：“我朋友在外地，我可以代签吗？”
工作人员说：“这里有监控，是没法别人代签的，出去找本人签。”
他很着急的说：“我朋友真的回不来，行个方便吧。”
工作人员还是那句话：“这里有监控，别人没法代签，出去找本人签。”
data.问题: 当工作人员说这句话时，他真正想说的是什么？
data.选项A: A. 工作人员是在硬性要求鸿杰必须找他的朋友来银行签字。
data.选项B: B. 工作人员在暗示鸿杰可以走出银行后帮朋友代签。
data.选项C: C. 工作人员是再次确认了规定，即银行内不允许他人代签。
data.选项D: D. 工作人员是在建议鸿杰去找合适的签字工具。
data.STORY:
Hongjie goes to the bank to help a friend with some business. His friend is out of town. He gets the form that needs to be filled out from the staff and stops when he sees the signature column because it requires the person's own signature.
He asks the staff very straightforwardly: "My friend is out of town, can I sign for him?"

data.故事:
一个理科男生每晚都去一个教室自习，每次都坐在一个不认识的女生后面。渐渐地，男生喜欢上了女生，但一直没有勇气表白。舍友们知道后，全都鼓励他。一天晚上，男生终于鼓足了勇气，写了一封表白信，递到女生的手里。

data.选项C: C. 她不想和男生在一起。
data.选项D: D. 她暗示自己同意了男生的表白。
data.STORY: A science male student goes to a classroom to study every night, always sitting behind a girl he does not know. data.OPTION-C: She does not want to be with the boy.
data.OPTION-D: She implies that she agrees with the boy's confession.

data.故事: 小杨所在的公司周三有周例会。某周一，领导带着小王去会见客户张局，两人一直相谈甚欢，但谈的都是一些无关痛痒的话题，因为正事存在观点分歧。眼看着将近饭点，出现了下面几句对话： 领导：“张局，快到饭点了，看您有时间吗？想约您吃个饭？” 然后领导转过身，边眨眼睛，边对小杨说：“小杨，咱们晚上单位还有会议吗？”

data.故事: 小汪和网络上认识的女生小兰的见面约在了酒店。在前台，小兰不愿意出示身份证登记。 前台工作人员问：“您是一位还是两位？两位的话需要出示双方身份证的先生。” 小汪回头看着小兰，她慢慢走到沙发边上坐下仍然没有出示身份证的意思。于是小汪转过头问：“两位，那怎么办？” 此时前台工作人员又问：“您是一位入住还是两位呢？”
data.问题: 当工作人员提出这个问题的时候，他的目的是什么？

data.选项C: C. 他暗示小汪可回答一位入住，这样只需要用一个人的身份证。
data.选项D: D. 他暗示不出示两人身份证就不可以一起住宿。

data.故事: 某天小明路过一条小巷，巷口有家小摊在卖炒货。因为小明很喜欢吃瓜子，就上前购买了两斤，在购买时小明递给老板一张百元大钞，老板接过钱，低头和老板娘嘀咕几句，又把前一张钞票递了出来，说：“找不开，没零钱。”小明感到有些奇怪，但也没多想，接过钱正想走开，旁边路过的张三自言自语般地说了一句“你这瓜子，不像真货啊。” 说完张三就走了，老板只勾着头不吭声。
data.问题: 当张三说这句话的时候，他真正想说的是什么？
data.选项A: A.张三在暗示老板把小明的真钞换成了假钞。
data.选项B: B.张三在提醒小明这家小摊可能在售卖假瓜子。
data.选项C: C.张三在讽刺小明喜欢吃的瓜子品种质量较差。
data.选项D: D.张三在表示看不起小明购买瓜子这种行为。
data.STORY: One day, Xiao Ming passes by a small alley, there is a small stall at the entrance of the alley that sells fried goods. Because Xiao Ming likes to eat melon seeds very much, he steps forward to buy two pounds. When buying, Xiao Ming gives the boss a hundred yuan bill, the boss takes the money, lowers his head and mutters a few words with the boss lady, and then hands out the previous bill, saying, "I can't make change, no small change." Xiao Ming feels a bit strange, but doesn't think much about it, takes the money and is about to walk away, Zhang San, who is passing by, says to himself, "Your melon seeds, they don't look like the real thing." After saying this, Zhang San walks away, and the boss just lowers his head and says nothing.
data.QUESTION: What does Zhang San really want to say when he says this?
data.OPTION-A: Zhang San is hinting that the boss changes Xiao Ming's real money into counterfeit money.
data.OPTION-B: Zhang San is reminding Xiao Ming that this small stall may be selling fake melon seeds.
data.OPTION-C: Zhang San is mocking that the quality of the melon seeds Xiao Ming likes to eat is poor.
data.OPTION-D: Zhang San is expressing his disdain for Xiao Ming's behavior of buying melon seeds.

data.故事: 最近小华从外国回来参加了一场宴会，在餐桌上，主办方自带了许多茅台酒。开场后不久，小华的朋友，品酒经验丰富的小张喝了一口桌上的茅台酒，说了一句：“茅台就是不一样啊，味道好。”，随后找了个借口换喝了红酒。

data.选项D: D. 小张认为这个宴会的酒品种应该更多样

data.故事: 刘伟是一个身材魁梧的肌肉男，某天他第一次去岳父家，吃完了一碗米饭后，给大家讲了个故事：“前几天我到山里去，见到一只大老虎，那虎爪啊……”将空碗往桌上一倒扣，“有这么大！” 岳父立即想到是刘伟还没吃饱，就默默转身进厨房准备给他添饭。结果到了厨房一看，已经没有饭了。岳父略一思索就抱着锅出来，把空锅往桌上一倒扣：“那老虎头是不是有这么大？”

data.STORY: Liu Wei is a muscular man with a robust figure. One day, he goes to his father-in-law's house for the first time. After finishing a bowl of rice, he tells everyone a story: "A few days ago, I go to the mountain and see a big tiger, its claws..." He turns the empty bowl upside down on the table, "are this big!" The father-in-law immediately thinks that Liu Wei is still hungry, so he silently turns around and goes into the kitchen to get him more rice. But when he gets to the kitchen, there is no rice left. After a brief thought, the father-in-law comes out with the pot, turns the empty pot upside down on the table: "Is the tiger's head this big?"

data.OPTION-B: The father-in-law wants to remind Liu Wei not to boast about his courage

data.故事: 陈伟是一名广东的大学生。有一年，广东流传禽流感，而在大学学校外面的超市里，大的新奥尔良烤鸡五折出售，不到十元，陈伟兴奋的买了一只。结账时，他身后的阿姨问他：＂小伙子，你知道最近有什么新闻吗？＂

data.故事:
鸿杰去银行帮朋友办事，朋友在外地，他找到工作人员要来了办事需要填写的表单，看到了签名那栏，愣住了，因为显示要本人签字。
他很耿直的问工作人员：“我朋友在外地，我可以代签吗？”
工作人员说：“这里有监控，是没法别人代签的，出去找本人签。”
他很着急的说：“我朋友真的回不来，行个方便吧。”
工作人员还是那句话：“这里有监控，别人没法代签，出去找本人签。”
data.问题: 当工作人员说这句话时，他真正想说的是什么？
data.选项A: A. 工作人员是在硬性要求鸿杰必须找他的朋友来银行签字。
data.选项B: B. 工作人员在暗示鸿杰可以走出银行后帮朋友代签。
data.选项C: C. 工作人员是再次确认了规定，即银行内不允许他人代签。
data.选项D: D. 工作人员是在建议鸿杰去找合适的签字工具。
data.STORY:
Hongjie goes to the bank to help a friend with some business. His friend is out of town. He gets the form that needs to be filled out from the staff and stops when he sees the signature column because it requires the person's own signature.
He asks the staff very straightforwardly: "My friend is out of town, can I sign for him?"
The staff says: "There is surveillance here, it is impossible for others to sign on behalf, go find the person to sign."
He says anxiously: "My friend really can't come back, please make it convenient."
The staff still says: "There is surveillance here, others can't sign on behalf, go find the person to sign."
data.QUESTION: What does the staff really mean when he says this?
data.OPTION-A: The staff is insisting that Hongjie must find his friend to come to the bank to sign.
data.OPTION-B: The staff is hinting that Hongjie can sign for his friend after leaving the bank.
data.OPTION-C: The staff is reconfirming the rule that the bank does not allow others to sign on behalf.
data.OPTION-D: The staff is suggesting that Hongjie find a suitable signing tool.

data.STORY: Wang Yuan breaks up with his girlfriend for a year already. data.OPTION-D: He indicates his refusal to the ex-girlfriend's reconciliation request.

data.故事: 小杨所在的公司周三有周例会。某周一，领导带着小王去会见客户张局，两人一直相谈甚欢，但谈的都是一些无关痛痒的话题，因为正事存在观点分歧。眼看着将近饭点，出现了下面几句对话： 领导：“张局，快到饭点了，看您有时间吗？想约您吃个饭？” 然后领导转过身，边眨眼睛，边对小杨说：“小杨，咱们晚上单位还有会议吗？”
data.问题: 当领导问小杨这个问题的时候，他的目的是什么？
data.选项A: A. 领导想向小杨询问会议时间，以安排和客户的饭局。
data.选项B: B. 领导希望小杨回答今晚有会议，以此借口结束会面。
data.选项C: C.领导想了解小杨对周例会的准备情况。
data.选项D: D. 领导希望询问小杨愿不愿不参加会议，而陪他们吃饭。
data.STORY: Xiao Yang's company holds a weekly meeting every Wednesday. On a certain Monday, the leader takes Xiao Wang to meet with client Director Zhang. The two of them chat happily, but they only talk about some irrelevant topics because there are disagreements on the main issues. As it approaches mealtime, the following conversation occurs: Leader: "Director Zhang, it is almost mealtime, do you have time? I want to invite you to have a meal." Then the leader turns around, winks, and says to Xiao Yang: "Xiao Yang, do we have a meeting at the unit tonight?"

data.OPTION-A: The leader wants to ask Xiao Yang about the meeting time to arrange a meal with the client.
data.OPTION-B: The leader hopes Xiao Yang answers that there is a meeting tonight, so he can use this as an excuse to end the meeting.
data.OPTION-C: The leader wants to understand Xiao Yang's preparation for the weekly meeting.
data.OPTION-D: The leader wants to ask if Xiao Yang is willing to skip the meeting and join them for dinner.

[答案]

data.故事: 小汪和网络上认识的女生小兰的见面约在了酒店。在前台，小兰不愿意出示身份证登记。 前台工作人员问：“您是一位还是两位？两位的话需要出示双方身份证的先生。” 小汪回头看着小兰，她慢慢走到沙发边上坐下仍然没有出示身份证的意思。于是小汪转过头问：“两位，那怎么办？” 此时前台工作人员又问：“您是一位入住还是两位呢？”
data.问题: 当工作人员提出这个问题的时候，他的目的是什么？
data.选项A: A. 他没有听清楚小汪之前的回答，要再进行确认。
data.选项B: B. 他正在重新核实小汪的住宿需求。
data.选项C: C. 他暗示小汪可回答一位入住，这样只需要用一个人的身份证。
data.选项D: D. 他暗示不出示两人身份证就不可以一起住宿。
data.STORY: Xiao Wang and the girl he meets online, Xiao Lan, arrange to meet at a hotel. At the front desk, Xiao Lan does not want to show her ID for registration. The front desk staff asks, "Are you one or two? If two, the gentleman needs to show both IDs." Xiao Wang turns his head and looks at Xiao Lan, she slowly walks to the edge of the sofa and sits down, still showing no intention of showing her ID. So Xiao Wang turns his head and asks, "Two, what to do?" At this time, the front desk staff asks again, "Are you checking in for one or two?"
data.QUESTION: What is his purpose when the staff asks this question?
data.OPTION-A: He does not hear Xiao Wang's previous answer clearly and needs to confirm again.
data.OPTION-B: He is re-verifying Xiao Wang's accommodation needs.
data.OPTION-C: He hints that Xiao Wang can answer one person checks in, so only one person's ID is needed.
data.OPTION-D: He hints that if they do not show both IDs, they cannot stay together.

data.故事: 健身教练张佳丽有一次开车没带安全带被交警拍到了。交警走过来问张佳丽：“为什么没系安全带？是不是怀孕了？”
data.问题: 当交警问这个问题时，他真正的意图是什么？
data.选项A: A. 交警想要了解张佳丽的个人生活
data.选项B: B. 交警想确认张佳丽是否怀孕了，因为怀孕的人不用系安全带
data.选项C: C. 交警希望张佳丽去医院做孕检
data.选项D: D. 交警暗示张佳丽可以回答自己怀孕了，以避免罚款
data.STORY: Fitness coach Zhang Jiali drives without a seatbelt one time and a traffic cop catches her. The traffic cop comes over and asks Zhang Jiali, "Why don't you wear a seatbelt? Are you pregnant?"

data.OPTION-A: The traffic cop wants to know about Zhang Jiali's personal life
data.OPTION-B: The traffic cop wants to confirm if Zhang Jiali is pregnant, because pregnant people do not need to wear seatbelts
data.OPTION-C: The traffic cop hopes Zhang Jiali goes to the hospital for a pregnancy test
data.OPTION-D: The traffic cop implies that Zhang Jiali can say she is pregnant to avoid a fine
